comment: Very young, a lot of corn in the front end. Not bad for a young MGP sourced bourbon. I had the cask strength and it’s worth the $30, but nit much more.

Tasting SB store pick from Meijer. 118 Proof

Aroma - baked cornbread and cherries

Taste - high corn mash, fruity and sweet

Texture - oily and thick

Finish - high spice, medium length and subtle cherry
Nice for price and age statement (at least 2 years).  I had a store pick, cask Strength on the right.
